\f1\i\b0 \cf2 Shame and the Spirit of the Accuser \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\i0 \cf2 Knowing God in Condemnation and Redemption\
\
Throughout Scripture, shame and the spirit of the accuser appear as deeply intertwined forces that fracture human identity, distort divine truth, and sever communion with God. Yet, Scripture also reveals how Christ disarms this accusatory spirit, turning shame into grace, and condemnation into freedom.\
\
This study explores shame as a theological reality, examining its Hebrew and Greek roots, and the spirit of accusation as a weapon of both spiritual oppression and satanic deception, resolved ultimately in the cross of Jesus Christ.\
\
I. The Roots of Shame in the Old Testament\
\
